","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"4","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 2 - River Bend","note":"A 10-15 minute walk beyond Deep Creek, River Bend is located on the right side of the point of a sharp bench 10 feet above the river. This site has a maximum group size of 4 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"no","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297400":{"location":[37.353126,-112.9505525],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"6","caravans":"no","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 3 - Right Bench","note":"A 10-15 minute walk beyond Deep Creek, River Bend is located on the right side of the point of a sharp bench 10 feet above the river. This site has a maximum group size of 6 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"required","static_caravans":"no","tents":"yes","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297401":{"location":[37.3516865,-112.949057],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"2","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 4 - Flat Rock","note":"Flat Rock is a 5-10 minute walk beyond Right Bench, located beside a large flat rock next to the river. The site is next to the rock, on a 6 foot high bench next to the canyon wall. This site has a maximum group size of 2 and is available for walk-up perm","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"no","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297402":{"location":[37.3503685,-112.9492],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"6","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 5 - Ringtail","note":"Flat Rock is a 5-10 minute walk beyond Right Bench, located beside a large flat rock next to the river. The site is next to the rock, on a 6 foot high bench next to the canyon wall. This site has a maximum group size of 2 and is available for walk-up perm","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"required","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297403":{"location":[37.3490981,-112.950437],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"12","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 6 - Kolob Creek","note":"At the confluence of Kolob Creek. The site is located on the right side, 20 feet above the river on a bench. This site has a maximum group size of 12 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"no","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297404":{"location":[37.3452796,-112.950661],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"6","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 7 - Box Elder","note":"A 10 minute walk beyond Kolob Creek. This site is located on the left about 30 feet up on a bench. This site has a maximum group size of 6 and is available for reservations online or on a walk-up basis.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"required","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297405":{"location":[37.3448007,-112.950664],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"6","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 8 - Boulder Camp","note":"Across the river from Box Elder, a 10 minute walk beyond Kolob Creek around a sharp bend. The access trail is to the right up slope about 50 feet. This site has a maximum group size of 6 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"no","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297406":{"location":[37.3400805,-112.954712],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"6","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 9 - Left Bench","note":"Across the river from Box Elder, a 10 minute walk beyond Kolob Creek around a sharp bend. The access trail is to the right up slope about 50 feet. This site has a maximum group size of 6 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"required","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297407":{"location":[37.3386127,-112.957419],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"6","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 10 - West Bend","note":"A 5 minute hike from Left Bench. This site is on a high bank located on a western bend. This site has a maximum group size of 6 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"no","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297408":{"location":[37.3333242,-112.955457],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"4","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 11 - Spotted Owl","note":"This sunny site is located on the left side, immediately after the first stream crossing. It is up a slope 10 feet above the river. This site has a maximum group size of 4 and is available for walk-up permit only.","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"no","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9109297409":{"location":[37.3320617,-112.957175],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","capacity:persons":"12","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 12 - High Camp","note":"High Camp is a 15-20 minute walk beyond Spotted Owl on a slow, difficult section of the river, 300 yards before Big Spring. The site is on the left side of the river on a 25 foot high bench in a stand of maple and Douglas-fir. It can be easy to miss. This","operator":"Zion National Park","reservation":"required","website":"https://www.nps.gov/zion/planyourvisit/backpackinginfo.htm"}},"9461939633":{"location":[37.2105925,-113.0553661],"tp":"CS","tags":{"access":"permit","backcountry":"yes","camp_site":"basic","capacity:persons":"6","fee":"yes","name":"Campsite 2 - Sl